Message.MsgText: CWFOR1000E=CWFOR1000E: The templateName parameter cannot be specified with either the templateServerNode or templateServerName parameters.
Message.Explanation: The user most either enter the templateName or the templateServerNode and templateServerName parameters.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the command with either the templateName option or the templateServerNode and the templateServerName options.

Message.MsgText: CWFOR1003E=CWFOR1003E: Matching template {0} could not be found.
Message.Explanation: A template could not be located with the name {0}
Message.UserResponse: Enter the name of valid template.

Message.MsgText: CWFOR1002E=CWFOR1002E: Cannot find server "{0}" on node "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The server that you are using as a template is not located on the node that you provided.
Message.UserResponse: Enter the name of valid server to be used as a template and the name of the node in which that server resides.

Message.MsgText: CWFOR1001E=CWFOR1001E: The templateServerNode and templateServerName parameters must both be specified.
Message.Explanation: When using the templateServerNode paremeter you must also specify the templateServerName.
Message.UserResponse: The templateServerNode parameters requires the templateServerName parameter to be enter as well.
